HEADWORD: Divaricator
<hw>Di*var`i*ca"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>One of the muscles which open the shell of brachiopods; a cardinal
muscle. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Brachiopoda</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

